  "instructions": [
    "Heat wok oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.",
    "Add the sliced onion and cook until crispy and golden, about 4 minutes.",
    "Add the minced garlic and cook for 1 minute, until fragrant.",
    "Add 1 cup of the Chiapas cheese blend and stir until melted and gooey, about 2 minutes.",
    "Add 1/4 cup of the sweet sherry and stir to combine, scraping the bottom of the pan.",
    "Season with cumin, smoked paprika, salt, and black pepper.",
    "Warm tortillas over a low flame or in the oven.",
    "Assemble the tacos with the crispy onion, melted cheese mixture, and a sprinkle of cilantro (if using)"
